{[showcards S:S4]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown.

You lead the \HJ, covered by dummy's \HQ and won by East's \HK. East wins the \HA at the second trick and continues with a small \H ruffed by South.

South then plays the \S4 from his hand. Do you play low? or play the \SJ to force dummy's \SA?

Play the \S3.

If South decides to finesse the \ST then you will still win the one \S trick which you are entitled to win. 

However, with South holding the \SQ it would be very logical for him to go up with the \SA then lead back toward his \SQ, playing East for the \SK. If he plays this way you will get two tricks and defeat the contract.}
[Play "W"]HJ

